column1: This file contains a list of all transaction outputs of the cluster identified by the following root address:
The cluster is also known by the following name:
Each line represents a transaction output which is either sent to the cluster or received by the cluster.
Transaction Hash: The 32 byte hash of the transaction that contains the output.
Index: The zero based index of the output in the transaction.
Block Height: The height of the blockchain where the transaction was confirmed.
Date: The date when the transaction was confirmed.
Receiving Address: If the output is received by this cluster then this will be the address in the cluster that received payment.
Peer Address: If the output is sent by this cluster then this will be the address in the peer cluster that payment was sent to.
Peer Cluster: The root address of the peer cluster which is being sent to or received from.
Peer Name: The name of the peer cluster if it has been given a name.
Peer Category: The category of the peer cluster if it has a category.
Received: If the output is received by this cluster then this will be the amount received.
Sent: If the output is sent from this cluster then this will be the amount sent.
USD value: The approximated USD value converted by using daily average prices. 0 if the price is unknown.
